Spelling: licence->license

According to my dictionary, "licence" is a British English spelling
whereas "license" is an American English spelling. By and large,
the Astropy project documentation appears to be written in American
English. This spelling change also makes the text consistent with
the name of the license directory.

modindex_common_prefix

A list of prefixes that are ignored for sorting the Python module index (e.g., if this is set to ['foo.'], then foo.bar is shown under B, not F). This can be handy if you document a project that consists of a single package. Works only for the HTML builder currently. Default is [].
